" width="1280" aria-labelledby="fig18" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 18</span> Foreign-body ingestion in a 38-year-old man with colicky abdominal pain. Coronal CT image shows a long linear hyperattenuating structure (arrow) in the mesentery. Pneumoperitoneum was not identified. At laparotomy, a fish bone was recovered and a sealed perforation of the terminal ileum was identified.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.314105065&amp;id=fig18">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.314105065/asset/images/105065fig19a.jpeg" height="1280" width="1277" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.314105065&amp;id=fig19a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig19b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.314105065/asset/images/105065fig19b.jpeg" height="1280" width="509" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 19b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.314105065&amp;id=fig19b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig20a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.314105065/asset/images/105065fig20a.jpeg" height="1133" width="1280" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 20a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.314105065&amp;id=fig20a">Down